TOPIC 11:
WATER
DURATION:
6 Periods
GENERAL OBJECTIVE:
By the end of this topic the learner should be able to state the properties of water.
SPECIFIC OBJECTIVE
CONTENT
TEACHING AND LEARNING
STRATEGIES
Learners should be able to:
• State the composition of water.
• Test for the products of burning organic matter.
Explain the experiment showing that water
contains hydrogen.
State the products of reaction of water and steam
with different metals.
List the reactivity series obtained from
metal/water reaction,
• Composition of water.
• The water cycle.
• Burning of organic matter (energy source).
• Water as an oxide of hydrogen.(Burning
hydrogen and a candle in air)
Reactions of metals with water/steam.(Na,
Ca, Mg with water and Mg, Zn, Fe with
steam)
Brain storm on the composition
of water.
Have a guided discussion on the
water cycle.
Carryout an experiment to
demonstrate that water is one of
the products formed when
organic fuels are burnt.
Carryout an experiment to show
water is an oxide of hydrogen.
Carryout experiment to show the
reaction between the given metal
and water/steam.
Assign the learners project work
in groups to design a reactivity
series based on the experiments
conducted above.
Have a guided discussion on the
reactivity series.
